Abstract = {While preparing an account of Crepidium (Orchidaceae) for Flora of
   Thailand, a new species was discovered on limestone hills in peninsular
   Thailand; it is described here as Crepidium falcifolium. It has
   previously been collected and identified as C. godefroyi, but is more
   similar to C. khasianum. We demonstrate that the new species differs
   from either in both vegetative and floral characters. A detailed
   description and illustrations are provided together with notes on
   taxonomy, habitat requirements, and conservation status.},
