Year = {1983},
Volume = {35},
Number = {2},
Pages = {120-125},
Abstract = {Examination of flowers from herbarium specimens of S. ovalis revealed 2
   kinds of column structure. Some plants, including the type, have flowers
   with a normally developed rostellum and viscidium; other plants that
   have flowers in which these structures are entirely lacking are
   described as S. ovalis var. erostellata var. nov. Self-pollination in
   the new variety was proven by pollinia removal and observation of plants
   in insect-proof cages. The var. erostellata has a somewhat smaller
   perianth with sepals 3,5-5 instead of 4-6 I mm long and is more common
   and more widespread than the typical variety.},
