Pages = {11+},
Abstract = {The description of the assortative pollination of Ophrys spp.
   (Orchidaceae) by sexually excited aculeate Hymenoptera males is based on
   many years of field observation and experimentation. The volatile
   compounds of the flowers responsible for this specific behavior release
   are probably mainly cyclic sesquiterpene alcohols and hydrocarbons.
   Processes of co-evolution may be assumed to have functioned in the
   creation of the Ophrys pollination groups.},
